## POST OFFICE SAVINGS ACCOUNT SCHEME

(Notified vide G.S.R. 921 (E) dated 12.12.2019 and further amended vide G.S.R. 257(E) dated 09.04.2021)

GSR.921 (E).In exercise of the powers conferred by section 3A of the Government Savings Promotion Act, 1873 (5 of 1873), the Central Government hereby makes the following Scheme,  namely:-

1.  Short  title  and  commencement.(1)  This  Scheme  may be called the Post Office Savings Account Scheme, 2019.
- (2)        It shall come into force on the date of its publication in the Official Gazette.
2. Definitions. -(1) In this Scheme, unless the context otherwise requires,-
4. (a)      'account' means an account opened under this Scheme;
5. (b)        'account holder' means an individual in whose name the Account is held;
6. (c)       'Act' means the Government Savings Promotion Act, 1873 (5 of 1873);
7. (d)       'Form' means forms appended to this Scheme;
8. (e)       'General Rules' means the Government Savings Promotion General Rules, 2018;
9. (f)        'year' means a period of twelve months commencing on the 1 st day of April.
- (2)          Words and expressions used herein but not defined shall have the meanings assigned to them in the Act and in the General Rules.
3.  Type  of  Account.(1)  An  account  may  be  opened  by  making  an  application  in  Form-1  by  the following:-
12. (a)        a single adult;
13. (b)        two adults jointly;
14. (c)        a guardian on behalf of a minor;
15. (d)       a guardian on behalf of a person of unsound mind;
16. (e)        a minor who has attained the age of ten years, in his own name:

Provided that only one account can be opened by an individual as a single account:

Provided further that an account under clause (e) can only be opened if an account under clause (c) does not exist in the name of the minor or vice versa .
